string 1:
When Extra Strike triggers, a circle will appear on the HUD.

{fc9Press {decision} when the circle reaches the center to cause a Strike Effect.}

This will activate various additional effects such as healing allies,
or applying status abnormalities on enemies.

{fc9Effects change depending on a Digimon's Attribute and Personality.}
Try out different combinations to use in battle.

Damage is calculated based on Attribute compatibility {fc9(the
compatibility matrix of {is28}{image(ui_icon_type_000)} Vaccine > {is28}{image(ui_icon_type_040)} Virus > {is28}{image(ui_icon_type_020)} Data)}
as well as Elemental Resistances and Traits.

{fc9Guarding greatly reduces damage until the Digimon's next turn.}

This battle command is useful when you can't avoid attacks from
an enemy with unfavorable compatibility or powerful Special Skills.

{fc9{is28}{image(ui_icon_type_000)} Vaccine}
{fc9{is28}{image(ui_icon_type_020)} Data}
{fc9{is28}{image(ui_icon_type_040)} Virus}
{fc9{is28}{image(ui_icon_type_060)} Free}
{fc9{is28}{image(ui_icon_type_080)} Variable}
{fc9{is28}{image(ui_icon_type_100)} Unknown}
In-Training I and II Digimon are {fc9{is28}{image(ui_icon_type_120)} No Data}.

You can confirm a Digimon's Attribute via their stats screen.

 - Favorable compatibility:{fc9 2x damage}
 - Unfavorable compatibility:{fc9 0.5x damage}
 - {is28}{image(ui_icon_type_120)} {fc9No Data}, {is28}{image(ui_icon_type_060)} {fc9Free}, {is28}{image(ui_icon_type_080)} {fc9Variable}, and {is28}{image(ui_icon_type_100)} {fc9Unknown} have no
favorability toward other Attributes.

{fc9"Digivolution" has been added to Aegiomon's battle commands.}

He can now undergo a special Digivolution only when in battle.

{fc9Aegiomon is able to equip the Crimson Dragon Data Fragment to
start the battle in a special Digivolved state.}

The power of Iliad's treasure has unlocked Aegiomon's potential,
meaning his true development starts now.

Your current objective will be displayed as a guide marker on the map.

{fc9Use the {menu} Navigation feature to keep the enlarged Map and mission 
objective displayed on-screen as you move around.}

Each Digimon possesses an affinity with each of the elements:

{is28}{image(ui_icon_skill_001)} Fire, {is28}{image(ui_icon_skill_002)} Ice, {is28}{image(ui_icon_skill_003)} Plant, {is28}{image(ui_icon_skill_004)} Water, {is28}{image(ui_icon_skill_005)} Electricity,
{is28}{image(ui_icon_skill_006)} Steel, {is28}{image(ui_icon_skill_007)} Wind, {Is28}{image(ui_icon_skill_008)} Earth. {is28}{image(ui_icon_skill_009)} Light, {is28}{image(ui_icon_skill_010)} Dark, and
{is28}{image(ui_icon_skill_000)} Null.

These affinities affect their elemental resistances, as per below.
{fc11◎}:{fc9 2x damage}
{fc11○}:{fc9 1.5x damage}
－: No effect
{fc2△}:{fc9 0.5x damage}
{fc2×}:{fc9 No damage}

These conditions affect Digimon during battles.

{fc9Digimon can only be affected by one at a time, although existing
status abnormalities may be overwritten by more powerful ones.}
Icons will be displayed next to stats affected by a status abnormality.

{fc9Please refer to "Status Abnormality Types & Effects" for more details.}

{fc9Poison}
The Digimon incurs poison damage at the end of its turn. It can
be cured immediately using items or skills.

{fc9Deadly Poison}
The Digimon incurs significant poison damage at the end of its
turn. It can be cured immediately using items or skills.

{fc9Confusion}
The Digimon may not be able to perform any actions during its turn.
It can recover immediately using items or skills.

{fc9Chaos}
The Digimon is unable to perform any actions during its turn. It can
recover when attacked, or by using items or skills.
